00:09:35.170 --> 00:09:38.950 align:middle line:84%
The psychological foundation for
all relationships in our life

00:09:38.950 --> 00:09:43.090 align:middle line:84%
is our primal relationship
to our mother and father.

00:09:43.090 --> 00:09:47.290 align:middle line:84%
These primal connections form
our personality, our strengths,

00:09:47.290 --> 00:09:51.730 align:middle line:84%
and our weaknesses, our
neuroses, and the hidden drives

00:09:51.730 --> 00:09:53.260 align:middle line:90%
in our lives.

00:09:53.260 --> 00:09:55.390 align:middle line:84%
Examining our
relationship patterns

00:09:55.390 --> 00:09:57.610 align:middle line:84%
with our parents
and family is one

00:09:57.610 --> 00:10:01.210 align:middle line:84%
of the first steps for the
psychological self-help inner

00:10:01.210 --> 00:10:04.570 align:middle line:84%
work which every person
must do in order for us

00:10:04.570 --> 00:10:08.740 align:middle line:84%
not to become trapped in our
own childhood conditioning.

00:10:08.740 --> 00:10:12.100 align:middle line:84%
Whatever we felt we needed and
did not receive from our mother

00:10:12.100 --> 00:10:15.880 align:middle line:84%
and father and family
becomes key inner conflicts

00:10:15.880 --> 00:10:19.270 align:middle line:84%
and neuroses in our lives
until we illuminate them

00:10:19.270 --> 00:10:22.870 align:middle line:84%
with consciousness and
dissolve these inner conflicts.

00:10:22.870 --> 00:10:25.840 align:middle line:90%


00:10:25.840 --> 00:10:27.940 align:middle line:84%
At the most
fundamental level, we

00:10:27.940 --> 00:10:30.910 align:middle line:84%
keep trying to recreate
our core traumas,

00:10:30.910 --> 00:10:32.860 align:middle line:84%
casting the people
we meet in our life

00:10:32.860 --> 00:10:36.510 align:middle line:84%
into roles in our
own psychodrama.

00:10:36.510 --> 00:10:40.230 align:middle line:84%
